The paper deals with a cake cutting game, which involves geometric objects such as points and rectangles. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves analyzing the number of points required to prevent Bob from gaining more than a certain fraction of the cake, which suggests that it may involve algorithms and data structures, leading to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as the second likely sub-category. The paper also involves game theory, as the players are trying to maximize their share of the cake, leading to cs.GT (Game Theory) as the third likely sub-category. The paper also involves combinatorial analysis, as it analyzes the number of points required to achieve a certain outcome, leading to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) as the fourth likely sub-category. Finally, the paper may involve computational complexity, as it analyzes the minimum number of points required to achieve a certain outcome, leading to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as the fifth likely sub-category.
